  "chunks": [
    {
      "chunk_text": "Hello, this is 6 Minute English from BBC Learning English. I'm Neil. And I'm Georgie.",
      "chunk_id": "88066906-abaf-46f9-968d-e4893191336b",
      "chunk_index": 0,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 85,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.238130"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "In this programme, we'll be asking",
      "chunk_id": "8d907a2c-f1c3-4c09-a4c9-4a865c27f2aa",
      "chunk_index": 1,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 34,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.240229"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "How much salt is too much? And as usual, we'll be learning some useful new vocabulary as well. Great. But first, I have a question for you, Neil. The reason it's difficult to know how much salt you consume is that it's hidden in food, especially processed food. So which of the following everyday foods do you think contains most salt? Is it a. Meat b. Bread c. Pasta Well, I'm going to guess that meat is",
      "chunk_id": "d215310d-fb48-44e8-8abd-b87bbca3b1b9",
      "chunk_index": 2,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 405,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "CI",
        "ROC",
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.242778"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "the saltiest of those foods. OK, Neil, I'll reveal the answer later in the programme. Marian Sambiva lives in Astana, the capital of Kazakhstan, a country where people eat on average 17 grams of salt a day. That's more than three times the amount recommended by the WHO. Here, Marian explains some of the reasons behind this to BBC World Service programme The Food Chain.",
      "chunk_id": "57ec408c-85f0-4758-84df-923114a90814",
      "chunk_index": 3,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 371,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "BI",
        "XP",
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.245281"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Besides improving its flavour,",
      "chunk_id": "cce5d64c-f601-461a-8836-fba56d357468",
      "chunk_index": 4,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 30,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.247366"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "so salt has a long and useful history.",
      "chunk_id": "3578e4b6-8f8f-4ce4-a51a-9ddc24e16bf7",
      "chunk_index": 5,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 38,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.249452"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Globally, governments are fighting this health risk in different ways.",
      "chunk_id": "b5b8fee5-eeb3-490e-8ce3-a94e017dac92",
      "chunk_index": 6,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 70,
      "enhanced_tags": [],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.251575"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Claire Collins is Professor of Nutrition at the University of Newcastle in Australia. Here, she explains more about these salt recommendations to BBC World Service programme The Food Chain.",
      "chunk_id": "3965e611-e845-46b0-8bd1-75555e3611d2",
      "chunk_index": 7,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 189,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "XP",
        "RSI",
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.253843"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Instead of arguing over grams of salt, Professor Collins thinks we should take a step back and look at the bigger picture.",
      "chunk_id": "c7e41273-5add-4a7e-a9b1-7f5e85215f4b",
      "chunk_index": 8,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 122,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "UI",
        "BI",
        "ES"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.256066"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "To consider the overall meaning of something, not just the details. Yes, the problem remains that overconsumption of salt is causing premature health problems, problems which are happening sooner than they should. By limiting salt and processed food, most people can enjoy long, healthy lives. And if you don't like your food unsalted, try adding herbs and spices instead. Well, speaking of salty foods, I think it's time to reveal the answer to my question, Neil.",
      "chunk_id": "befcdd27-2147-402b-ba3a-7a421192aa93",
      "chunk_index": 9,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 464,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "ROC",
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.258670"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "If you remember, I asked you which everyday food contains most salt. And I guessed it was meat. Which was the correct answer. Meat contains the highest amount of salt, around 19%, followed by bread with 14% and pasta with 7%. OK, let's recap the vocabulary we've learned in this programme, starting with the verb to preserve food, meaning to do something to stop it rotting so it can be eaten later.",
      "chunk_id": "948ab1b9-c201-439e-b5bd-23d633d4a728",
      "chunk_index": 10,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
      "original_filename": "RSS_262026947_podcast_1304_Less salt better health.json",
      "collection_name": "RSS_262026947",
      "chunk_length": 399,
      "enhanced_tags": [
        "OTT",
        "ES",
        "AI"
      ],
      "tagged_at": "2025-07-10T14:45:09.261208"
    },
    {
      "chunk_text": "Dairy products are foods such as cheese and butter, which are made from milk. The idiom to look at the bigger picture means to consider the overall meaning of something, rather than the specific details.",
      "chunk_id": "f9d94f77-42f8-4f72-bcf3-e42eea92e3e9",
      "chunk_index": 11,
      "episode_id": "6865015b66c1a4e8d11766a6",
